[SN]TITLE[SN]
Joel Coleman and Ivan Paurevic: Huddersfield Town sign duo

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Huddersfield Town have signed Oldham goalkeeper Joel Coleman and FC Ufa midfielder Ivan Paurevic for undisclosed fees.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Both players have agreed three-year contracts with the Championship side.
Coleman, 20, made 34 appearances in all competitions for the League One Latics last season.
Former Croatia Under-21 international Paurevic, 24, played under Town boss David Wagner at Borussia Dortmund II before joining Russian club Ufa.
